events.name: Next '18 Extended Tallinn
events.description:
We will be meeting each-other for first time. This meetup is hosted by the Toggl time tracking tool, who are happily running on Google Cloud themselves!

Important notes:
- Please bring your notebook - we will spend some time to explore google cloud monitoring fundamentals using Qwiklabs.com browser-based hands on lab.
- There will be photo and video recording of the event. Videos and photos from event will be published in internet, and may be used for promotions by us, by venue host (Toggl) and according to Google plus terms of service - by Google itself.
- There will be no snacks or drinks on venue during event, be sure to plan accordingly!

Tentative agenda for event:

17:45 - 17:55 - Welcome && Intro.

18:00 - 18:55 - Qwiklabs. You will not need credit card, but you will need laptop to participate in this hands-on tutorial. We will start working on [Cloud Architecture Quest](https://google.qwiklabs.com/quests/24). We will see how easy is to monitor machine and aggregate logs in "Stackdriver Qwik Start". If we have time left, we also look around "Getting Started with Cloud KMS" lab together. It will be possible to try other labs from home after event.

19:00 - 20:30 Live stream of actual Next 18 keynote: [Bringing the Cloud to You](https://cloud.withgoogle.com/next18/sf/sessions/session/219899)

20:30 - 21:00 Closing and cleaning :)

events.name: Cloud Dinner
events.description:
Highly experimental pre-alpha event, to connect passionate people around Google Cloud. We meet and just talk about what hurts and what was epic win in our past Cloud experience.

No official program and no sponsors.

Please do not sign up unti you are sure you will be able to come.

events.name: Cloud Dinner #2: DevFest on air afterparty
events.description:
To build on warm discussion from our previous Cloud Dinner we will meet in center of Tallinn (exact place will be announced separately) to have some snack and talk about our favorite cloud :)

Date is 12. December, on that day there will be online event https://devfest.withgoogle.com/events/devfestonair18 This event is concluding seasons of DevFest events across the globe. You can expect several hours of content (divided into two days to cover multiple timezones) and three separate tracks: Cloud; Mobile; Voice, Web & more.

Sessions will cover multiple products such as Android, Google Cloud Platform, Firebase, Google Assistant, Flutter, machine learning with TensorFlow, and mobile web. That seems to be nice content lineup, and after watching we will surely have something to discuss at same evening.

As last time - please signup only if you are sure that you will be able to attend us on evening of 12 december.
events.how_to_find_us: We booked large table at http://poobel.ee/

events.name: Cloud Dinner #3: Toit's city
events.description: As usual we will meet and spend hour-or-two talking on all cloud topics and related things. There is no strict agenda, and exact location will be revealed closer to event date, depending on anticipated number of attendees.
events.how_to_find_us: I'll make sure that cloud community logo is visible on the edge of our table

events.name: Cloud Dinner #4: Google  IO 2019
events.description:
It's time to meet again, to have cozy dinner and discuss cloud everything.

And there is great topic available, just in 3 hours Google I/O starts bringing ton of announcements, tips and tricks about google platform. I am attending this year I/O so will bring insider experiences and emotions that are not obtainable through livestream, directly to our cloud dinner.

Location will be announced 1 week before event, hope to see you all on our dinner, and don't forget to watch livestream of event at https://events.google.com/io/live/
events.how_to_find_us:
We have table reservation at Mr. Mauruse Pub  for 'Ervin Weber / Google Cloud'. Map Link:  https://goo.gl/maps/ycAJFgboUXyMebno7 
Table is in small room, to the left right after entrance.

events.name: Cloud Dinner: Tastes better with AIY Project
events.description:
This event is joint effort with devclub.ee community, AIY kits are still en route but they should arrive in time for 25th June.

- We will try to build Cloud Speech-to-Text service demo and see what it takes teach camera to recognise simple objects using power of google cloud.

NB For this joint event Eventbrite registration form is used instead of usual RSVP in this service. https://www.eventbrite.com/e/devclub-73-von-stackelberg-hotel-tickets-63737236791

(people in waitlist received registration link before any public announcements, to ensure head start).

events.name: Cloud Dinner #5: What's next?
events.description:
Our usual informal meeting, to chit-chat and discuss Google Cloud affairs, problems and successes. You can join us if you are already using cloud, and have stories or questions, or if you are just planning to do so and are looking for more information.

Points of interest:

- Google Cloud Next '19 UK (November 19-21) - What would you like to hear?
- Google Stadia launches in 2 months, Hamina datacenter is near, but does it affect us?
- Upcoming rename of this group - Oppotunity or Loss?
events.how_to_find_us: Table in http://maurus.ee/kontakt/ is booked to Ervin Weber's name, and as usual you will see the logo once you reach us.

events.name: Cloud Dinner #6:  Year Complete?!!
events.description:
Last social event of the year will be an rewind of things happened during the year. There has been plenty of announcements in this year from Google - tell us what was your favourite so far.

Our community did grow to be 200 members strong, and hopefully it is just a beginning. Yet we would need some extra input from you - what is your wish, how could this community help you? Come and dream BIG, or just share your story.

Location: Humalakoda, Balti jaama turg

events.name: Community  Speedrun Challenge #1:  BigQuery Basics for Data Analysts
events.description:
This is online-only event consisting of webinar and week-long access to self-paced labs at QwikLabs.com.

The Community Speedrun Challenge is a training program that will run in February where you’ll have the opportunity to join four Speedruns and get hands-on experience with tools like Kubernetes, Assistant, BigQuery our Cloud Run, Every Speedrun is open for a week to give you the ability to finish all labs in your best time, scoring more points and winning prizes.

Find more information and register here: bit.ly/speedrunchallenge0220
